<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,1537,1960]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1862,1888]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Remarks.</emphasis>
The purported record in 
<collectingCountry box="[596,657,1862,1888]" name="Chile" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Chile</collectingCountry>
based on a parasitized female (Linnavuori &amp; DeLong, 1977) is questionable, as noted in their publication. A 
<typeStatus box="[601,704,1898,1924]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this, the type species of the genus, was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Paradell, S. &amp; Zahniser, J. N." pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="293 - 295" refId="ref80914" refString="Paradell, S. &amp; Zahniser, J. N. (2018) Designation of a neotype for Clorindaia hecaloides Linnavuori (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae: Faltalini). Zootaxa, 4532 (2), 293 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4532.2.9" type="journal article" year="2018">Paradell &amp; Zahniser (2018)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
